HpjzYvoNX5_8RE=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering file organization**\\n\\nI think I need to write a new file and include the necessary imports. I should check the method names for adherence to checkstyle rules and ensure the package-private test methods are okay. Top-level public classes seem fine, but I'll need to check if all top-level test classes must be public as well. I should also remember to add buildArg and use the edit function to finalize writing the file.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_1gJt4wD9w6JSVHhj1EhbBYdZ|fc_0934f8640c641dc6016a04a10b28088197a002e8d4814964c6", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/commons-httpclient/commons-httpclient/3.0/src/test/java/commons_httpclient/commons_httpclient/PostMethodTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage commons_httpclient.commons_httpclient;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\n\nimport org.apache.commons.httpclient.NameValuePair;\nimport org.apache.commons.httpclient.methods.PostMethod;\nimport org.apache.commons.httpclient.methods.RequestEntity;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class PostMethodTest {\n    private static final String POST_METHOD_CLASS_NAME =\n            \"org.apache.commons.httpclient.methods.PostMethod\";\n\n    @Test\n    void compilerGeneratedClassLookupResolvesPostMethodType() throws Throwable {\n        MethodHandles.Lookup lookup = MethodHandles.privateLookupIn(\n                PostMethod.class,\n                MethodHandles.lookup());\n        MethodHandle classLookup = lookup.findStatic(\n                PostMethod.class,\n                \"class$\",\n                MethodType.methodType(Class.class, String.class));\n        String postMethodClassName = new StringBuilder(\"org.apache.commons.httpclient.methods\")\n                .append(\".PostMethod\")\n                .toString();\n\n        Class<?> resolvedClass = (Class<?>) classLookup.invoke(postMethodClassName);\n\n        assertThat(resolvedClass).isEqualTo(PostMethod.class);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void freshClassLoaderInitializationRunsLegacyClassHelper() throws Exception {\n        try (PostMethodClassLoader classLoader = newPostMethodClassLoader()) {\n            Class<?> methodClass = Class.forName(\n                    POST_METHOD_CLASS_NAME,\n                    true,\n                    classLoader);\n\n            assertThat(methodClass.getName()).isEqualTo(POST_METHOD_CLASS_NAME);\n            if (NativeImageSupport.isNativeImageRuntime()) {\n                assertThat(methodClass).isSameAs(PostMethod.class);\n            } else {\n                assertThat(methodClass.getClassLoader()).isSameAs(classLoader);\n            }\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void constructorInitializesPostMethodDefaults() throws Exception {\n        PostMethod method = new PostMethod(\"/submit?source=test\");\n\n        assertThat(method.getName()).isEqualTo(\"POST\");\n        assertThat(method.getPath()).isEqualTo(\"/submit\");\n        assertThat(method.getQueryString()).isEqualTo(\"source=test\");\n        assertThat(method.getParameters()).isEmpty();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void formParametersAreEncodedAsRequestEntity() throws Exception {\n        PostMethod method = new PostMethod(\"/submit\");\n        method.addParameter(\"alpha\", \"one two\");\n        method.addParameter(new NameValuePair(\"symbol\", \"+&=\"));\n\n        RequestEntity entity = method.getRequestEntity();\n        ByteArrayOutputStream output = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        entity.writeRequest(output);\n\n        assertThat(method.getParameter(\"alpha\").getValue()).isEqualTo(\"one two\");\n        assertThat(entity.getContentType()).isEqualTo(PostMethod.FORM_URL_ENCODED_CONTENT_TYPE);\n        assertThat(output.toString(StandardCharsets.US_ASCII.name()))\n                .isEqualTo(\"alpha=one+two&symbol=%2B%26%3D\");\n    }\n\n    private static PostMethodClassLoader newPostMethodClassLoader() {\n        URL location = PostMethod.class.getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource().getLocation();\n        return new PostMethodClassLoader(\n                new URL[] {location},\n                PostMethodTest.class.getClassLoader());\n    }\n\n    private static final class PostMethodClassLoader extends URLClassLoader {\n        private PostMethodClassLoader(URL[] urls, ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(urls, parent);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            synchronized (getClassLoadingLock(name)) {\n                if (POST_METHOD_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                    Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n                    if (loadedClass == null) {\n                        loadedClass = findClass(name);\n                    }\n                    if (resolve) {\n                        resolveClass(loadedClass);\n                    }\n                    return loadedClass;\n                }\n                return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 340, "output": 1199, "cacheRead": 31744, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33283, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0,